metadata.name: Euphonic #208
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: Dynamic generations #243
metadata.description:
A classic cellular automata updates its state with a static rule based on the state of its neighbor.

This collection was created with cellular automata with an extension of that idea. Here the state and the rule are updated based on the state of its neighbor, here the rule changes in every iteration, here the rule is dynamic.

That change moves cellular automata to another level of complexity.

metadata.name: Pebbles #27
metadata.description:
Generative series in six different ranges of 30 colors each that are combined with 150 colors forming a wall. "The Pebbles" series pays tribute to these first ancestral wall constructions in dry stone without concrete to hold them together. It is an ancient technique that dates back to the Stone Age.

This series of generatives NFTs is born from the drawings presented in Milan at the Galería Patricia Armocida. They are composed of stone blocks in 6 series of 50 originals in which 30 colors per range are combined with 150 secondary range colors in infinite shapes.

http://www.nuriamora.com/serie-piedras/

The first Range is Blue.


Coded in P5js.

Source code based on Roni Kaufman previous work and used under a collaborative agreement.

metadata.name: Stairs #17
metadata.description:
Algorithmically generated stairs. Inspired by Dutch graphic artist M.C. Escher.

Arrangement, style and color set are unique in each edition.

However:
Any edition can generate an infinite amount of arrangements & styles and allows you to cycle through the color sets, so that you can find your perfect piece. 
The preview is based on the initial, randomized arrangement & style.


Created in Vanilla JS on Canvas2D

Controls:
R - Generate Stairs
B - Change Background
C - Change Color
D - Change Style
A - Restart Animation
S - Download Image


DUTCH AUCTION:

metadata.name: let me fall #104
metadata.description:
A study of form, empty spaces, panic attacks, asymmetry, tinnitus, chaos, and the never-ending journey to obtain imperfection. 

30 Matisse-inspired palettes.

2-6 – increase resolution.

“f” – add more noise to iteration at current resolution.
“n” – redraw at current resolution without noise.
“s” – save export.

Please be patient while drawing at higher resolutions, it can take quite a while.

Created with p5js.
